		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Sep 11th 10:25 AM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1094867176843372558&num=2&post=1&replyto=1094912720203081981"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1094912720203081981></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=4283"><span id="">Tassoth, Eater of Souls</span></a><b><span id=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />506 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.74]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Tassoth&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>To do quests you find NPC's and hail them, you will see some dialogue and generally words in [boxes]. If you then said &quot;What boxes?&quot; the npc would carry on and tell you a bit more untill you get a quest. Generally they involve collecting items and combining/handing in to that NPC. So you can get quests for gear, money, spells and every other item you would need in the game. <br /> <br />Selling items to PC's is more difficult because you need to have items people want to buy. At low level this is unlikely to be the case since you don't have access to many things, but silks are always wanted and farmable by every one. If you kill lots of spiders to level up, you can then sell the silks for a bit of money. <br /> <br />The best way to make money is to become a bazaar whore, although this involves spending lots of time in the bazaar watching prices and buying good items cheaply and trying to sell for a profit. This also involves you having some money to start with. You should find that doing some quests and killing monsters will provide you with enough money to get along with, just keep care of it since if you fritter it away you'll never be able to upgrade.</p>
